from scipy.stats import mode
from additive.feature_functions import feature_functions_functions as feat_funs
def image_stats(x):
    funs = {k: v for k, v in feat_funs.items()}
    return compute({k: delayed(v)(x) for k, v in funs.items()})[0]

In [7]:
def min_max_scale(x, a=0, b=1):
    mn, mx = x.min(), x.max()
    rng = b - a
    out = (x - mn)/(mx-mn)
    return out * rng + a

def get_equalized_stats(image):
    scaled_image = min_max_scale(image, 0, 255).astype('uint8')
    equalized_image = cv2.equalizeHist(scaled_image)
    return image_stats(equalized_image)

import matplotlib as mpl
mpl.rcParams.update(mpl.rcParamsDefault)
font = {'size'   : 13}
matplotlib.rc('font', **font)

left, width = 0.2, 0.85
bottom, height = 0.1, 0.65
spacing = 0.005


rect_scatter = [left, bottom, width, height]
rect_histx = [left, bottom + height + spacing, width, 0.2]
rect_histy = [left + width + spacing, bottom, 0.2, height]
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))
ax = fig.add_axes(rect_scatter)
ax_hist = fig.add_axes(rect_histy, sharey=ax)

N = 1000
for name, sub_im, dx, dy in zip(names, sub_ims, [-20, 10, 30], [0, 45, 60]):
    x = np.arange(sub_im.shape[1])
    ax.plot(x+dx, sub_im[500]-sub_im.min(), label=name, linewidth=3, alpha=.8)
    ax_hist.hist(sub_im[500]-sub_im.min(), orientation='horizontal', bins=20, density=True, alpha=.8)
    ax_hist.set_yticks([])
    ax_hist.set_xticks(np.arange(0, .24, .04).round(2))
ax.legend(loc='upper left')
fig.savefig("../data/paper/figures/polishedVsHalfVsMorePolishedWithHist.png", dpi=300)
